cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.CC 

This paper discusses the interplay between content distribution and traffic engineering in network-CDNs, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also touches upon security issues related to content distribution (cs.CR) and the optimization of network costs (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the placement and routing of content within the network (cs.DC) and the use of demand-oblivious schemes (cs.CC) for traffic engineering.
